HEADWORD: Host plant
<hw>Host plant</hw>. <fld>(Agric.)</fld> <def>A plant which aids,
shelters, or protects another plant in its growth, as those which are
used for nurse crops.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hostry</ent>⟦br⟧
